09/10/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The government issued an international warrant Wednesday (8 October) for a local politician suspected of links to the rebel Albanian National Army. Idajet Beqiri, 49, leader of the Party of National Unity, is wanted for incitement and support for the extremist group, which has claimed responsibility for a number of attacks in Serbia and Macedonia.
In other news Wednesday, the government ordered increased security at major state institutions in advance of Sunday's local elections. Special police commandos would be situated in front of key buildings to ensure public order. (AFP, MakFax - 08/10/03)
